hpnicfConfig.name: hpnicfConfig

revisions.description: Initial revision of this MIB module.

hpnicfConfig.description: This MIB contains objects for managing the system configuration. It contains the model used to represent configuration data that exists elsewhere in the system and in peripheral devices. There are no constraints on this MIB.

ConfigOperationType.name: ConfigOperationType
ConfigOperationType.description: Specify operation types on configuration. Currently, following types of operation are provided: running2Startup(1): Update the saved configuration (startup) file used currently with the current configuration running in the system. This operation is equivalent to the [save] command from command line. If current startup configuration file does not exist, then the default startup configuration file is created to save the data and this becomes the current startup configuration file. startup2Running(2): Update the current configuration running in the system with the saved configuration (startup) file used currently. The commands in the file are executed as if they had been entered via the command line. If the current startup configuration file does not exist, the operation will fail with the error opFileOpenError(13). running2Net(3): Send the current configuration running in the system to the network using the specified file transfer protocol. net2Running(4): Update the current configuration running in the system with a remote file from the network using the specified file transfer protocol. The commands in the file are executed as if they had been entered via the command line. net2Startup(5): Download a remote file to the local system using the specified file transfer protocol and replace the saved configuration (startup) file used currently. If current startup configurationfile does not exist, the default startup configuration file is created to save the data and this becomes the current startup configuration file. startup2Net(6): Send the saved configuration (startup) file used currently to the network using the specified file transfer protocol. If the current startup configuration file does not exist, the operation will fail with the error opFileOpenError(13).

ConfigOperationStateType.name: ConfigOperationStateType
ConfigOperationStateType.description: The status of the specified operation. opInProgress : Specified operation is active. opOperationSuccess : Specified operation is supported and completed successfully. opInvalidOperation : Command invalid or command/protocol/device combination unsupported. opInvalidProtocol : Invalid protocol specified. opInvalidSourceName : Invalid source file name specified. opInvalidDestName : Invalid target name specified. opInvalidServerAddress : Invalid server address specified. opDeviceBusy : Specified device is in use and locked by another process. opDeviceOpenError : Invalid device name. opDeviceError : Device read, write or erase error. opDeviceNotProgrammable : Device is read-only but a write or erase operation was specified. opDeviceFull : Device is filled to capacity. opFileOpenError : Invalid file name; file not found in partition. opFileTransferError : File transfer was unsuccessful; network failure. opFileChecksumError : File checksum in Flash failed. opNoMemory : System running low on memory. opAuthFail: Invalid user name or password. opTimeOut : File transfer was timeout. opUnknownFailure : Failure unknown. opInvalidConfigFile: Invalid configration file. opSlaveFull : Operation is fail for the slave don't have enough space. opCopyToSlaveFailure : Operation is fail when copy file to the slave.

hpnicfCfgRunModifiedLast.name: hpnicfCfgRunModifiedLast
hpnicfCfgRunModifiedLast.description: The object records the value of sysUpTime when the current configuration running in the system was last modified. The value will be changed immediately after system detects the current configuration has been changed.

hpnicfCfgRunSavedLast.name: hpnicfCfgRunSavedLast
hpnicfCfgRunSavedLast.description: The object records the value of sysUpTime when the current configuration running in the system was last saved. If the value of the object is smaller than hpnicfCfgRunModifiedLast, the current configuration has been modified but not saved.

hpnicfCfgStartModifiedLast.name: hpnicfCfgStartModifiedLast
hpnicfCfgStartModifiedLast.description: The object records the value of sysUpTime when the saved configuration used currently was last modified. It may have been modified by a save of the current configuration running in the system or other methods such as copy.

hpnicfCfgLogLimitedEntries.name: hpnicfCfgLogLimitedEntries
hpnicfCfgLogLimitedEntries.description: The object shows the maximum number of rows in hpnicfCfgLogTable. The value supported by the system is 10.

hpnicfCfgLogDeletedEntries.name: hpnicfCfgLogDeletedEntries
hpnicfCfgLogDeletedEntries.description: The total number of rows deleted from hpnicfCfgLogTable.

hpnicfCfgLogWantBackup.name: hpnicfCfgLogWantBackup
hpnicfCfgLogWantBackup.description: Decide whether to backup the value of objects about hpnicfCfgLog.

hpnicfCfgLogTable.name: hpnicfCfgLogTable
hpnicfCfgLogTable.description: Table for logging configuration operation in device.

hpnicfCfgLogIndex.name: hpnicfCfgLogIndex
hpnicfCfgLogIndex.description: Index of the table beginning from 1.

hpnicfCfgLogTime.name: hpnicfCfgLogTime
hpnicfCfgLogTime.description: Specify the sysUpTime when the config log was generated.

hpnicfCfgLogSrcCmd.name: hpnicfCfgLogSrcCmd
hpnicfCfgLogSrcCmd.description: Specify the source command which brought the log. Currently we provide the types of source: 1.cmdLine(1):configure log instigated by command line. 2.snmp(2):configure log instigated by snmp. 3.other(3):configure log instigated by other source unknown.

hpnicfCfgLogSrcData.name: hpnicfCfgLogSrcData
hpnicfCfgLogSrcData.description: The source of the configuration data event. erase erasing destination runningData operational data alive commandSource the command source itself startupData what the system will use next reboot local local NVRAM or flash netFtp FTP network transfer hotPlugging board is inserted or pulled out on line

hpnicfCfgLogDesData.name: hpnicfCfgLogDesData
hpnicfCfgLogDesData.description: The destination for the configuration data event. unknown unknown runningData operational data alive commandSource the command source itself startupData what the system will use next reboot local local NVRAM or flash netFtp FTP network transfer hotPlugging board is inserted or pulled out on line

hpnicfCfgLogTerminalType.name: hpnicfCfgLogTerminalType
hpnicfCfgLogTerminalType.description: Specifies the terminal type. If hpnicfCfgLogSrcCmd is not 'cmdLine', use 'notApplicable'. The value list: notApplicable(1): no meaning at this time. unknown(2): unknown terminal type. console(3): console interface. terminal(4): generic terminal. virtual(5): virtual terminal such as telnet. auxiliary(6): auxiliary interface.

hpnicfCfgLogTerminalUser.name: hpnicfCfgLogTerminalUser
hpnicfCfgLogTerminalUser.description: The name of logging user which is available when hpnicfCfgLogSrcCmd is 'cmdLine'. Other, a zero length string.

hpnicfCfgLogTerminalNum.name: hpnicfCfgLogTerminalNum
hpnicfCfgLogTerminalNum.description: Specifies the terminal number. If hpnicfCfgLogSrcCmd is not 'cmdLine', use '-1'

hpnicfCfgLogTerminalLocation.name: hpnicfCfgLogTerminalLocation
hpnicfCfgLogTerminalLocation.description: The location of logging user which is available when hpnicfCfgLogSrcCmd is 'cmdLine'. Other, a zero length string.

hpnicfCfgLogCmdSrcAddress.name: hpnicfCfgLogCmdSrcAddress
hpnicfCfgLogCmdSrcAddress.description: The address from which a request comes when the value of hpnicfCfgLogSrcCmd is 'snmp(2)'. The ip address of the remote system connected when the value of hpnicfCfgLogTerminalType is 'virtual'. Other, the value of 0.0.0.0. This object is replaced by hpnicfCfgLogCmdSrcAddrRev for it only support IPv4.

hpnicfCfgLogVirHost.name: hpnicfCfgLogVirHost
hpnicfCfgLogVirHost.description: The host name of remote system connected if hpnicfCfgLogTerminalType has the value of 'virtual'. Other, a zero length string.

hpnicfCfgLogUserName.name: hpnicfCfgLogUserName
hpnicfCfgLogUserName.description: The user name used when hpnicfCfgLogSrcData or hpnicfCfgLogDesData has the value of 'netFtp'. Other, a zero length string.

hpnicfCfgLogServerAddress.name: hpnicfCfgLogServerAddress
hpnicfCfgLogServerAddress.description: The remote server address when hpnicfCfgLogSrcData or hpnicfCfgLogDesData has the value of 'netFtp'. Other, a value of 0.0.0.0. This object is replaced by hpnicfCfgLogServerAddrRev for it only support IPv4.

hpnicfCfgLogFile.name: hpnicfCfgLogFile
hpnicfCfgLogFile.description: The current configuration file name when hpnicfCfgLogSrcData has the value of 'netFtp',and hpnicfCfgLogDesData has the value of 'startupData'. Other, a zero length string.

hpnicfCfgLogCmdSrcAddrType.name: hpnicfCfgLogCmdSrcAddrType
hpnicfCfgLogCmdSrcAddrType.description: The type of IP address for the hpnicfCfgLogCmdSrcAddrRev.

hpnicfCfgLogCmdSrcAddrRev.name: hpnicfCfgLogCmdSrcAddrRev
hpnicfCfgLogCmdSrcAddrRev.description: The address from which a request comes when the value of hpnicfCfgLogSrcCmd is 'snmp(2)'. The ip address of the remote system connected when the value of hpnicfCfgLogTerminalType is 'virtual'. Other, the value of 0.0.0.0.

hpnicfCfgLogCmdSrcAddrVPNName.name: hpnicfCfgLogCmdSrcAddrVPNName
hpnicfCfgLogCmdSrcAddrVPNName.description: The VPN instance of this operation uses.

hpnicfCfgLogServerAddrType.name: hpnicfCfgLogServerAddrType
hpnicfCfgLogServerAddrType.description: The type of IP address for the hpnicfCfgLogServerAddrRev.

hpnicfCfgLogServerAddrRev.name: hpnicfCfgLogServerAddrRev
hpnicfCfgLogServerAddrRev.description: The remote server address when hpnicfCfgLogSrcData or hpnicfCfgLogDesData has the value of 'netFtp'. Other, a value of 0.0.0.0.

hpnicfCfgLogServerAddrVPNName.name: hpnicfCfgLogServerAddrVPNName
hpnicfCfgLogServerAddrVPNName.description: The VPN instance of this operation uses.

hpnicfCfgFirstTrapTime.name: hpnicfCfgFirstTrapTime
hpnicfCfgFirstTrapTime.description: Time when the first trap is sent.

hpnicfCfgOperateGlobalEntryLimit.name: hpnicfCfgOperateGlobalEntryLimit
hpnicfCfgOperateGlobalEntryLimit.description: The maximum number of copy entries that may be held in hpnicfCfgOperateTable. A particular setting does not guarantee that much data can be held.

hpnicfCfgOperateEntryAgeOutTime.name: hpnicfCfgOperateEntryAgeOutTime
hpnicfCfgOperateEntryAgeOutTime.description: The number of minutes an unactive hpnicfCfgOperateEntry SHOULD be kept in the hpnicfCfgOperateTable before it is active. The object is a fator taken account of when it needs delete some rows make room in hpnicfCfgOperateTable.

hpnicfCfgOperateResultGlobalEntryLimit.name: hpnicfCfgOperateResultGlobalEntryLimit
hpnicfCfgOperateResultGlobalEntryLimit.description: The maximum number of copy entries that may be held in hpnicfCfgOperateResultTable. A particular setting does not guarantee that much data can be held.

hpnicfCfgOperateIndex.name: hpnicfCfgOperateIndex
hpnicfCfgOperateIndex.description: The unique index value of a row in this table.

hpnicfCfgOperateType.name: hpnicfCfgOperateType
hpnicfCfgOperateType.description: Specify the type of operation on configuration.

hpnicfCfgOperateProtocol.name: hpnicfCfgOperateProtocol
hpnicfCfgOperateProtocol.description: If the value of hpnicfCfgOperateType is running2Net,net2Running,net2Startup or startup2net, this node specify the protocol to be used for file transfer . The default protocol is ftp if no protocol is specified. And for other value of hpnicfCfgOperateType , this object may be ignored by the implementation. when clusterftp or clustertftp is selected, the hpnicfCfgOperateServerAddress needn't be set, the server address can be acquired automatically, the value of hpnicfCfgOperateServerAddress is uncertain during operation. both member switch and commander switch can use them if they support HGMP v2.

hpnicfCfgOperateFileName.name: hpnicfCfgOperateFileName
hpnicfCfgOperateFileName.description: When the object of hpnicfCfgOperateType has the value of net2Startup, net2running or running2Net,the value must be specified. The file name may include the path if applicable. If the value of hpnicfCfgOperateType is net2Startup or net2running, this node specify the source file name of transfers.If the value of hpnicfCfgOperateType is running2Net , this node specify the destination file name of transfers. When hpnicfCfgOperateType has the value of startup2net,the object may not be created instead of using the file name of startup configuration file.

hpnicfCfgOperateServerAddress.name: hpnicfCfgOperateServerAddress
hpnicfCfgOperateServerAddress.description: When the operation type is running2Net,net2Running,net2Startup or startup2net , the ip address of the ftp/tftp server from/to which to download/upload must be specified. Values of 0.0.0.0 or FF.FF.FF.FF are not permitted. This object is replaced by hpnicfCfgOperateSrvAddrRev for it only support IPv4.

hpnicfCfgOperateUserName.name: hpnicfCfgOperateUserName
hpnicfCfgOperateUserName.description: When the operation type is running2Net,net2Running,net2Startup or startup2net , the user name for the ftp server from/to which to download/upload should be specified. The object must be created if hpnicfCfgOperateProtocol has the value of ftp.

hpnicfCfgOperateUserPassword.name: hpnicfCfgOperateUserPassword
hpnicfCfgOperateUserPassword.description: When the operation type is running2Net,net2Running,net2Startup or startup2net , the user password for the ftp server from/to which to download/upload should be specified. The object must be created if hpnicfCfgOperateProtocol has the value of ftp.

hpnicfCfgOperateEndNotificationSwitch.name: hpnicfCfgOperateEndNotificationSwitch
hpnicfCfgOperateEndNotificationSwitch.description: Specifies whether or not a notification should be issued on the completion of the operation.

hpnicfCfgOperateRowStatus.name: hpnicfCfgOperateRowStatus
hpnicfCfgOperateRowStatus.description: The status of this table entry. When the status is active all the object's value in the entry is not allowed to modified.

hpnicfCfgOperateServerPort.name: hpnicfCfgOperateServerPort
hpnicfCfgOperateServerPort.description: When the operation type is running2Net, net2Running, net2Startup or startup2Net, this node is used for specifying the remote port number. If the value is 0 or not specified, the known port number will be used.

hpnicfCfgOperateSrvAddrType.name: hpnicfCfgOperateSrvAddrType
hpnicfCfgOperateSrvAddrType.description: The type of IP address for hpnicfCfgOperateSrvAddrRev.

hpnicfCfgOperateSrvAddrRev.name: hpnicfCfgOperateSrvAddrRev
hpnicfCfgOperateSrvAddrRev.description: When the operation type is running2Net,net2Running,net2Startup or startup2net , the ip address of the ftp/tftp server from/to which to download/upload must be specified.

hpnicfCfgOperateSrvVPNName.name: hpnicfCfgOperateSrvVPNName
hpnicfCfgOperateSrvVPNName.description: The VPN instance of this operation uses.

hpnicfCfgOperateResultTable.name: hpnicfCfgOperateResultTable
hpnicfCfgOperateResultTable.description: A table of config-operation requests result.

hpnicfCfgOperateResultEntry.name: hpnicfCfgOperateResultEntry
hpnicfCfgOperateResultEntry.description: The result entries of configuration operation requests.

hpnicfCfgOperateResultIndex.name: hpnicfCfgOperateResultIndex
hpnicfCfgOperateResultIndex.description: The index of Table, which is an incremental integer. The maximum value of the node is 2147483647. The agent should wrap the value to 1 and flush all the existing entries when the maximum value is reached.

hpnicfCfgOperateResultOptIndex.name: hpnicfCfgOperateResultOptIndex
hpnicfCfgOperateResultOptIndex.description: The operation index in the hpnicfCfgOperateTable.

hpnicfCfgOperateResultOpType.name: hpnicfCfgOperateResultOpType
hpnicfCfgOperateResultOpType.description: The operation type in the hpnicfCfgOperateTable.

hpnicfCfgOperateState.name: hpnicfCfgOperateState
hpnicfCfgOperateState.description: The operation state type in the hpnicfCfgOperateTable.

hpnicfCfgOperateTime.name: hpnicfCfgOperateTime
hpnicfCfgOperateTime.description: Record the time taken for the operation. This object will be like a stopwatch, starting when the operation starts, and stopping when the operation completes.

hpnicfCfgOperateEndTime.name: hpnicfCfgOperateEndTime
hpnicfCfgOperateEndTime.description: The value of sysUpTime when the configuration operation is finished.

hpnicfCfgOperFailReason.name: hpnicfCfgOperFailReason
hpnicfCfgOperFailReason.description: The failure reasons of configuration operation.

hpnicfCfgExecuteOperateResultEntryLimit.name: hpnicfCfgExecuteOperateResultEntryLimit
hpnicfCfgExecuteOperateResultEntryLimit.description: The maximum number of ConfigOperationType entries that may be held in hpnicfCfgExecuteResultTable. A particular setting does not guarantee that much data can be held.

hpnicfCfgExecuteResultTable.name: hpnicfCfgExecuteResultTable
hpnicfCfgExecuteResultTable.description: A table of configuration execute result.

hpnicfCfgExecuteResultEntry.name: hpnicfCfgExecuteResultEntry
hpnicfCfgExecuteResultEntry.description: The result entries of configuration execute operation.

hpnicfCfgExecuteResultIndex.name: hpnicfCfgExecuteResultIndex
hpnicfCfgExecuteResultIndex.description: The index of Table, which is an incremental integer. The maximum value of the node is 2147483647. The agent should wrap the value to 1 and flush all the existing entries when the maximum value is reached.

hpnicfCfgExecuteResultOptIndex.name: hpnicfCfgExecuteResultOptIndex
hpnicfCfgExecuteResultOptIndex.description: The configuration execute operation index in the hpnicfCfgExecuteResultTable.

hpnicfCfgExecuteResultOpType.name: hpnicfCfgExecuteResultOpType
hpnicfCfgExecuteResultOpType.description: The operation type in the hpnicfCfgExecuteResultTable.

hpnicfCfgExecuteState.name: hpnicfCfgExecuteState
hpnicfCfgExecuteState.description: Record the status of the specified operation.

hpnicfCfgExecuteTime.name: hpnicfCfgExecuteTime
hpnicfCfgExecuteTime.description: Record the time of the execution starts.

hpnicfCfgExecuteEndTime.name: hpnicfCfgExecuteEndTime
hpnicfCfgExecuteEndTime.description: Record the time of the execution is finished.

hpnicfCfgReset.name: hpnicfCfgReset
hpnicfCfgReset.description: Reboot the device with the default configuration.

hpnicfCfgReset2.name: hpnicfCfgReset2
hpnicfCfgReset2.description: normal:do nothing. reset :reboot the device with the default configuration. 'normal' will be returned when getting. This node differs from hpnicfCfgReset in value.

hpnicfCfgManEventlog.name: hpnicfCfgManEventlog
hpnicfCfgManEventlog.description: The object calculates the checksum on the current config per 10 minutes and even if it is different from the saved config but if a trap has been sent with the same checksum then don't send again until the checksum is different.

hpnicfCfgOperateCompletion.name: hpnicfCfgOperateCompletion
hpnicfCfgOperateCompletion.description: When create hpnicfCfgOperateTable successfully, a notification may be generated.

hpnicfCfgInvalidConfigFile.name: hpnicfCfgInvalidConfigFile
hpnicfCfgInvalidConfigFile.description: When the configuration file is invalid, this notification will be generated.

hpnicfConfigManCompliance.name: hpnicfConfigManCompliance
hpnicfConfigManCompliance.description: The statement of compliance for those implementing the configuration management MIB.

hpnicfCfgManLogGroup.name: hpnicfCfgManLogGroup
hpnicfCfgManLogGroup.description: A collection of objects configuration log group.
